summary:
The Security Council:
Reaffirms previous resolutions on Western Sahara, particularly 1108 (1997), 1292 (2000), 1301 (2000), 1309 (2000), 1324 (2000), 1342 (2001), and 1308 (2000);
Recalls principles of the Convention on the Safety of UN and associated personnel;
Welcomes the Secretary-General's report (S/2001/398) and supports the Personal Envoy's role;
Supports MINURSO's efforts to implement the Settlement Plan for a free, fair and impartial referendum;
Noting unresolved differences between parties on the Settlement Plan,
1. Extends MINURSO's mandate until 30 June 2001, expecting parties to work towards resolving problems and finding a mutually acceptable solution under the Personal Envoy's auspices;
2. Requests the Secretary-General to assess the situation before the mandate ends;
3. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
